quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  54,9,"The people of Noah denied before them, for they denied Our servant and said, “Possessed!” And he was reproved"
  54,10,"Then he called upon his Lord, “Truly I am overcome. Help!”"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of the sky with pouring water
  54,12,"and We caused the earth to burst forth with springs, such that the waters met for a matter determined"
  54,13,Then We carried him upon a thing of planks and nails
  54,14,coursing under Our Eyes as a recompense for one who was rejected
  54,15,And indeed We left it as a sign; so is there any who remembers
  54,16,"How, then, were My Punishment and My warnings"
  54,17,And indeed We have made the Quran easy to remember; so is there any who remembers
  54,18,"Ad denied. How, then, were My Punishment and My warnings"
  54,19,Truly We sent upon them a howling wind on a day of incessant misfortune
  54,20,tearing out people as if they were uprooted palm trunks
  54,21,"How, then, were My Punishment and My warnings"
  54,22,And indeed We have made the Quran easy to remember; so is there any who remembers
  54,23,Thamud denied the warnings
  54,24,"They said, “Shall we follow a single human being from among us? Then we would surely be astray and mad"
  54,25,"Has the reminder been cast upon him from among us? Nay, he is an insolent liar.”"
  54,26,On the morrow they will know who is the insolent liar
  54,27,Behold! We are sending the she-camel as a trial for them; so watch them and be patient
  54,28,And inform them that the water is to be divided among them—each share of drink equitably proportioned
  54,29,"Then they called their companion, and he took in hand and hamstrung [her]"
  54,30,"How, then, were My Punishment and My warnings"
  54,31,"Truly We sent upon them a single cry, and they were like a fence maker’s dry sticks"
  54,32,And indeed We have made the Quran easy to remember; so is there any who remembers
  54,33,The people of Lot denied the warnings
  54,34,"Truly We sent upon them a torrent of stones, save the family of Lot, whom We delivered at dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We requite whosoever gives thanks
  54,36,"And indeed he had warned them of Our assault, but they disputed the warnings"
  54,37,They had sought to lure him from his guests; so We blotted out their eyes. So taste My Punishment and My warnings
  54,38,And indeed an enduring punishment greeted them early in the morning
  54,39,So taste My Punishment and My warnings
  54,40,And indeed We have made the Quran easy to remember; so is there any who remembers
  54,41,And indeed the warnings came unto the House of Pharaoh
  54,42,"They denied Our signs—all of them; so We seized them with the seizing of One Mighty, Omnipotent"
  54,43,Are your disbelievers better than those? Or have you some exemption in the scriptures
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We are a host victorious!”"
  54,45,"The whole shall be routed and they will turn [their] backs"
  54,46,"Nay! The Hour is their tryst, and the Hour is more calamitous and more bitter"
  54,47,Truly the guilty are astray and mad
  54,48,"On the Day they are dragged upon their faces into the Fire, “Taste the touch of Saqar.”"
  54,49,Truly We have created everything according to a measure
  54,50,"And Our Command is naught but one, like the blinking of an eye"
  54,51,We have indeed destroyed the likes of you; so is there any who remembers
  54,52,Everything that they have done is in the scriptures
  54,53,everything small and great is inscribed
  54,54,Truly the reverent are amidst Gardens and a stream
  54,55,upon a seat of truth before an Omnipotent King